      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm in a massive rush. our HFT engine is lagging because of this sorting logic. i need a python function `optimize_order_flow(orders)` that sorts a list of dictionaries by `price` (descending) and then by `timestamp` (ascending). \n\nhere are the sample orders i'm seeing in the logs right now:\norders = [\n    {'id': 'tx_1', 'price': 150.25, 'timestamp': 1625097600},\n    {'id': 'tx_2', 'price': 150.50, 'timestamp': 1625097605},\n    {'id': 'tx_3', 'price': 150.25, 'timestamp': 1625097590}\n]\n\nthe expected output for these is:\n[{'id': 'tx_2', 'price': 150.50, 'timestamp': 1625097605}, {'id': 'tx_3', 'price': 150.25, 'timestamp': 1625097590}, {'id': 'tx_1', 'price': 150.25, 'timestamp': 1625097600}]\n\ncan u just write the function real quick? it needs to be robust and pass our internal validator, we're running the tests in 5 mins.",
