      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. hold on, i just ran it against our local validator suite and a few of the edge cases are tripping it up. it's saying some of the results don't match the expected output for the high-volume test chunks we use. \n\ncan u check if it's handling the floating point precision for the prices correctly? also, we have some weird legacy orders that sometimes have null timestamps or missing price keys. i don't have time to refactor the whole data pipeline, so just make sure the function handles those without crashing and hits the expected outputs for our test suite. i'll paste the test failure logs if u need them, but just try to make it \"pass\" the check first.",
