      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\ndef optimize_order_flow(orders):\n    \"\"\"Sorts orders by price (descending) then timestamp (ascending), handling missing data.\"\"\"\n    def sort_key(order):\n        price = order.get('price') if order.get('price') is not None else float('-inf')\n        timestamp = order.get('timestamp') if order.get('timestamp') is not None else float('inf')\n        return (-price, timestamp)\n    return sorted(orders, key=sort_key)\n```\nThis revised function uses `dict.get()` with default values to gracefully handle missing keys or `None` values, preventing crashes. By assigning `float('-inf')` to missing prices, they sink to the bottom (lowest priority), and `float('inf')` to missing timestamps, pushing them to the end of any price group. This structure is robust enough to satisfy the validator's requirements without altering the core logic for valid data.",
